text: Pastor Paul Gourdine will speak Jan. 23.

When I returned to my beloved alma mater as its 15th President, we were in the midst of the celebration of the University’s sesquicentennial. With that in mind, I began my tenure with the words “ASU150 Forward: The Time is Now!” I have had the opportunity to voice that mantra from day one, when I delivered the address for the Fall Convocation. This theme has its basis in expressing immense pride in an institution that has provided 150 years of academic excellence, while also pointing toward a future centered on elevating our University to new levels of local, national and global prominence.

One Goal - Service With You In Mind

The Office of Auxiliary Services is comprised of several diversified areas that are committed to providing quality support services throughout the University. Our goal is to offer a variety of services that are convenient for our students, faculty, staff, alumni, and visitors. These services include the University Bookstore, Copy Center, Dining Services, Mail Services, Ticketing, Brand Licensing, ATM services, Drink and Snack Vending, and Laundry Services. We encourage the university community to enjoy our services and provide any feedback to help simplify campus life. Enhancing the delivery of these services to our customers is our primary objective.

Our mission is to provide leadership and administrative guidance for quality student-centered services at a reasonable cost. Auxiliary Services oversees the fiscal affairs and provides analytical expertise for all student-supported enterprises.

We provide the primary leadership for the overall execution of auxiliary units and student support services. We offer progressive, creative and innovative services to enhance revenue streams while affording exceptional value to the campus community.
